{
  "texts": [
    "As AI evolves to proficiently craft distinct literary and visual artifacts, the debate may intensify around the custodianship of intellectual property [59].The utilization of AI by educators, students, or authors to conceive or enhance content invites a re-examination of conventional concepts of creativity.",
    "The core question becomes: To whom does the resultant work belong?",
    "Is it the originator who initiated the process or the AI that elaborated upon those beginnings?",
    "These considerations extend beyond traditional moral territories, influencing the authenticity and appraisal of academic work and publications.",
    "This scenario necessitates a re-evaluation of assessment practices within educational spheres, including language education, especially with regard to the contributions and involvement of AI in the creative process.As the language educational community incorporates AI into the generative process, it is critical to define and adhere to ethical protocols."
  ]
}